      <section eId="sec_CC-2034">
        <num>CC 2034</num>
        <heading>2034.  Nullity of a provision</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 2034.  Nullity of a provision
Nullity of a provision does not render the whole contract null unless, from the nature of the provision or the intention of the parties, it can be presumed that the contract would not have been made without the null provision.</p>
        </content>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=109293</p>
